My specific doubt is on the topic: clarification on points reduction

My doubt is:
Recently I have submitted my programming graded assignments. In the grading system there are two parts Public Test Case and Private Test Case. As per my understanding the Public Test Case evaluates the given program solution on test run basis and Private Test Case is evaluated based on the actual submission of the assignment. I cannot understand why t

he Private Test Case results are reduced by one point in some graded assignments which I submitted and the method of evaluation for programming assignments is not mentioned anywhere in the portal or anywhere else. The video on submitting the graded programming assignments also did not clear the above mentioned doubts. Kindly clear my doubt on the above points and help me to understand how the points are reduced and the programming assignments are evaluated.

I faced a few issues during the DBMS OPPE and with the final assignment grading that I would like to seek clarification on:

  1. OPPE Python‑PostgreSQL Question:
    While attempting the Python‑PostgreSQL question, I imported all the required libraries and followed the correct syntax. However, during compilation, the query was marked as “invalid syntax,” even though the compiler suggested the keyword while typing. I successfully passed 100/100 test cases in the SQL question just b

efore this, so I’m concerned that this might affect my performance. While it’s possible I made an unintentional mistake, I would be grateful if the logs for my attempt could be reviewed to confirm the issue.

  • Laptop Restriction During OPPE:
    Due to serious performance issues with my older laptop, I used a newer device to take the exam. However, the exam link didn’t allow access and showed that only the previously registered laptop could be used. Since the exam is already scre

en- and video-recorded, I was unsure why this restriction applies. I seek clarification on what should be done in cases where the original device becomes too slow or non-functional.

  • Final Graded Assignment Average:
    I noticed that my final average for the graded assignments is showing as 60%, whereas I received 85% in one assignment which was actually my lowest among all 10. This seems inconsistent, and I kindly request a recheck of the average calculation.

p>I double-checked my Python‑PostgreSQL code and ensured correct syntax and library usage. I’ve also reviewed the assignment scores and tried comparing them to the final average. Despite this, the issues remain unclear to me, which is why I am posting here for clarification and help from the support team.

In this question, for A = [[1 0 0] [0 1 0] [0 0 1]], Ax = x, Ay = y, Az = z and all x, y, z are eigenvectors of A. Th

is also satisfies A = A^T.

For A = [[1 1 0] [1 1 1] [0 1 1]], Ay = (2, 3, 2) != λy. This also satisfies A = A^T.
